The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                 
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has said that Sachin Tendulkars view of splitting ODI matches into four innings with 25 overs each, was a sensible one which can revive popularity of the format.    
	Sultan Rana, chief of PCBs domestic cricket department, backed the proposal to split one-day international matches into four innings. If the International Cricket Council (ICC) allows its members to experiment with this new format, we will definitely be keen to try it out because our domestic structure is tailor-made for this new concept, Rana said.      
	Appointments  
	Calcutta: Former India pacer Javagal Srinath will share the Match Referees responsibilities with Jeff Crowe and Roshan Mahanama in the ensuing Champions Trophy in South Africa, according to an International Cricket Council (ICC) release Sunday. The on-field responsibilities will be shared by ICC the Elite panel umpires.      
	Cologne: Jeev Milkha Singh finally broke par and turned in an improved four-under 68 in the third round to rise to the tied 32nd spot, but SSP Chowrasia languished at the bottom in the Mercedes-Benz golf Championship here. Swede Hanson Peter blasted a five-under 67 to grab the lead.      
	Neel no more   
	Calcutta: Noel da Lima Leitao, 52, a football commentator, was found dead in his hotel room on Sunday. He probably suffered a heart attack. We have sent his body for autopsy for an official confirmation of the reason behind his death, a police officer said.      
	New Delhi: CGF president Michael Fennel, miffed with the capitals tardy preparation for the 2010 Commonwealth Games, has sought Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs intervention to put things in order.      
	JCT win  
	New Delhi: Striker Baljit Sahni missed three sitters before striking in the 62nd minute to guide JCT Phagwara to a 1-0 victory over ONGC in the the Durand Cup on Sunday.                                                                                                                                                                   
